 auteurism, and genre while tracing the relationship between film and history, Hollywood politics and censorship, and exile and (re)migration.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aMotion picture producers and directorszGreat BritainvBiography. 0aMotion pictureszUnited StatesxForeign influences. 0aMotion pictureszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aPolitical refugeeszGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / United States / 20th Century.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311066586440uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/gemn1667840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231536523423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780231536523.jpg  a978-3-11-066586-4  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles